  "root_text": {
    "iti41:0.1": "Itivuttaka 41 ",
    "iti41:0.2": "Dukanipāta ",
    "iti41:0.3": "Dutiyavagga ",
    "iti41:0.4": "Paññāparihīnasutta ",
    "iti41:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti41:2.1": "“Te, bhikkhave, sattā suparihīnā ye ariyāya paññāya parihīnā. ",
    "iti41:2.2": "Te diṭṭheva dhamme dukkhaṁ viharanti savighātaṁ saupāyāsaṁ sapariḷāhaṁ; ",
    "iti41:2.3": "kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā duggati pāṭikaṅkhā. ",
    "iti41:2.4": "Te, bhikkhave, sattā aparihīnā ye ariyāya paññāya aparihīnā. ",
    "iti41:2.5": "Te diṭṭheva dhamme sukhaṁ viharanti avighātaṁ anupāyāsaṁ apariḷāhaṁ; ",
    "iti41:2.6": "kāyassa bhedā paraṁ maraṇā sugati pāṭikaṅkhā”ti. ",
    "iti41:2.7": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti41:2.8": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti41:3.1": "“Paññāya parihānena, ",
    "iti41:3.2": "passa lokaṁ sadevakaṁ; ",
    "iti41:3.3": "Niviṭṭhaṁ nāmarūpasmiṁ, ",
    "iti41:3.4": "idaṁ saccanti maññati. ",
    "iti41:4.1": "Paññā hi seṭṭhā lokasmiṁ, ",
    "iti41:4.2": "yāyaṁ nibbedhagāminī; ",
    "iti41:4.3": "Yāya sammā pajānāti, ",
    "iti41:4.4": "jātibhavaparikkhayaṁ. ",
    "iti41:5.1": "Tesaṁ devā manussā ca, ",
    "iti41:5.2": "sambuddhānaṁ satīmataṁ; ",
    "iti41:5.3": "Pihayanti hāsapaññānaṁ, ",
    "iti41:5.4": "sarīrantimadhārinan”ti. ",
    "iti41:6.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti41:6.2": "Catutthaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti41:0.1": "So It Was Said 41 ",
    "iti41:0.2": "The Book of the Twos ",
    "iti41:0.3": "Chapter Two ",
    "iti41:0.4": "Bereft of Wisdom ",
    "iti41:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti41:2.1": "“Those sentient beings are truly bereft, mendicants, who are bereft of noble wisdom. ",
    "iti41:2.2": "They live unhappily in this very life—with distress, anguish, and fever—",
    "iti41:2.3": "and when the body breaks up, after death, they can expect a bad rebirth. ",
    "iti41:2.4": "Those sentient beings are not bereft who are not bereft of noble wisdom. ",
    "iti41:2.5": "In this very life they’re happy—free of distress, anguish, and fever—",
    "iti41:2.6": "and when the body breaks up, after death, they can expect a good rebirth.” ",
    "iti41:2.7": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti41:2.8": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti41:3.1": "“See the world with its gods, ",
    "iti41:3.2": "bereft of wisdom, ",
    "iti41:3.3": "habituated to name and form, ",
    "iti41:3.4": "imagining this is truth. ",
    "iti41:4.1": "Wisdom is best in the world, ",
    "iti41:4.2": "as it leads to penetration, ",
    "iti41:4.3": "through which one rightly understands ",
    "iti41:4.4": "the ending of rebirth and continued existence. ",
    "iti41:5.1": "Gods and humans envy them, ",
    "iti41:5.2": "the Buddhas, ever mindful, ",
    "iti41:5.3": "of laughing wisdom, ",
    "iti41:5.4": "bearing their final body.” ",
    "iti41:6.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti41:2.1": "Te → te ca kho (?) ",
    "iti41:4.2": "nibbedhagāminī → nibbānagāminī (ne4:302 [Vibhaṅga/ Otaraṇahāravibhaṅga]) ",
    "iti41:5.3": "hāsapaññānaṁ → sapaññānaṁ (pts-vp-pli1); hāsupaññānaṁ (aṭṭha.) "
  },
